.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.env
.env.local
node_modules/
.state/

# Local gstack tooling state (headless browser / QA); not part of the
# framework and never committed.
.gstack/

# In consumer repos, `/spades-onboard` injects committed copies of the
# framework's docs and examples under `.spades/docs/` and `.spades/examples/`.
# In THIS repo (the framework itself) the canonical copies under `docs/`
# and `examples/` are the source of truth, so we ignore any residual
# `.spades/docs/` or `.spades/examples/` that a local pre-guard onboarding
# run may have created. Bundle A's self-onboard guard prevents this
# going forward; this is belt-and-braces.
.spades/docs/
.spades/examples/

# Private learnings are captured by `/spades-learn` when the human
# classifies an entry as NOT public-safe. They stay on local disk for
# the team but must never be committed — they may reference internal
# systems, credentials paths, or security details that should not leak
# into public forks. See .claude/skills/spades-learn/SKILL.md.
.spades/learnings/private/

# HTML renderings of Scopes and Plans are a regeneratable read-only view
# produced by `bin/spades-render` (v1.6+). The Markdown is canonical; the
# `.html` siblings need not be committed. See docs/FRAMEWORK.md §HTML Rendering.
.spades/**/*.html

# Panel-review reports written by `/spades-review` (v2.0.0+). Each run
# persists its full report to `.spades/reviews/<slug>-<date>.md` as a
# local audit artefact. They can carry repository and architectural
# detail and are not committed — the inline digest is the shareable
# view. See .claude/skills/spades-review/SKILL.md § Presenting the Report.
.spades/reviews/

# Machine-local handoff config written by `/spades-onboard` — holds the
# terminal-emulator choice for `/spades-handoff`, which is specific to the
# developer's machine (one teammate uses iTerm2, another Terminal.app).
# The committed `.spades/config` carries the shared handoff settings; this
# file never is. See .claude/skills/spades-handoff/SKILL.md.
.spades/handoff.local
